---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="Disability Does Not Limit Kindness | OAKonsult"
	description="A boy with cerebral palsy stood so a mother could sit. Behind children like him are parent carers raising world-changers."
	path="/blog/disability-does-not-limit-kindness"
>
	<article>
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container" style="max-width: 780px;">
				<p class="section-kicker reveal">Blog &middot; February 12, 2026</p>
				<h1 class="reveal" style="--delay: 0.05s;">Disability Does Not Limit Kindness</h1>
				<p class="muted-copy reveal" style="--delay: 0.08s;">
					It reveals strength most of us overlook.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container" style="max-width: 780px;">
				<div class="reveal">
					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						On a train, a boy with cerebral palsy &mdash; whose body already works harder than
						most &mdash; chose to stand so a mother carrying her baby could sit.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						Let that sink in.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						He didn't have to. It wasn't easy. But empathy made him rise.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						Too often, society sees disability and assumes limitation. But what we witnessed
						was leadership. Character. Compassion in action.
					</p>

					<div class="callout callout--gold" style="margin: 1.5rem 0;">
						<p style="line-height: 1.9; font-weight: 600;">
							Behind children like him are parent carers who have poured love, resilience,
							advocacy, and invisible strength into raising humans who see beyond themselves.
						</p>
					</div>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						Parent carers are not just surviving appointments, systems, therapies, and
						sleepless nights. They are raising world-changers.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						But who is holding them?
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						That's why OAKonsult exists. Because behind every strong child is a carer who
						also deserves support, space, and restoration.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-forest); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600;">
						Kindness is not limited by disability. And support should never be limited
						for carers either.
					</p>

					<div class="callout-actions" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
						<a class="button button-primary" href="/get-involved">Get Involved</a>
						<a class="button button-ghost" href="/donate">Donate</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</article>
</Layout>
